		<h3>Daily Fiction</h3>
		<h1>The Palm House</h1>
		<h2>By Gwendoline Riley</h2>
		<div class="img-excerpt-container">
			<div class="img-container"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/The_Palm_House_efb0923b-ec0e-4fcc-93bb-8c87996f18b2.jpg" alt="The Palm House"></div>
			<div class="excerpt-container"><div class="excerpt"><em>The following is from Gwendoline Riley's </em>The Palm House<em>. Riley was born in London in 1979.  She is the author of seven novels, including </em>First Love, My Phantoms,<em> and most recently, </em>The Palm House<em>. In 2018, the </em>Times Literary Supplement<em> named her one of the twenty best British and Irish novelists working today.</em></div></div>
		</div>
